  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak the <strong>skewers</strong> in water (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>,<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>(save the rest for later!) and 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105155119-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105155119-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105155119-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105155119-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1629105155119-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and transfer to a clean plate to cool – this is your <strong>coconut rice</strong></p><p>Reserve the pot and heat the grill to medium-high</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105162399-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105162399-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105162399-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105162399-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1629105162399-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>peanuts</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[all] </span>the <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>half</strong> the <strong>crispy onions </strong>(save the rest for garnish), <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>remaining chicken stock mix</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2? Save the remaining cayenne pepper for another recipe!</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and blitz until a paste forms – this is your <strong>suya-style marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105169771-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629105169771-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
